summary: SummaryHighlightsClean IngredientsCruelty FreeVeganAdd shape and lift to your features with the Morphe Shapelifter Micro Contour Stick. With a super-slim tip and built-in sharpener, this sculpting stick provides controlled, targeted application. The longwearing, creamy formula glides on smoothly and blends seamlessly to naturally enhance.
details: DetailsFeaturesSuper-slim contouring stickEffortlessly precise applicationSmooth-gliding, richly pigmented formulaAll-day wear**Based on a 32-person clinical study.Research Results100% agreed it's creamy, lightweight, and blends effortlessly without harsh lines.*97% agreed it melts into skin while providing rich color payoff and a natural finish.*97% agreed its precision tip allows for controlled application94% agreed it creates the illusion of a real shadow without looking muddy or orange.**Based on a 32-person consumer perception study.Key IngredientsMade with antioxidant-rich vitamin E, known to hydrate and soften skin.Item 2644116How To UseTo add depth and dimension to your forehead, apply it just under your hairline.To lift cheeks, glide it under your cheekbones.To slim and refine your nose, trace along your nose sides and tip.To define lips, outline your lip line and inside your cupid's bow.To chisel your jawline, trace where there's natural shadowing.IngredientsIsononyl Isononanoate, Triethylhexanoin, Silica, Dimethicone, Synthetic Wax, Octyldodecanol, Dimethicone Crosspolymer, Microcrystalline Wax (Cera Microcristallina, Cire microcristalline), Caprylyl Glycol, Hydroxyacetophenone, Polyhydroxystearic Acid, Triethoxycaprylylsilane, Tocopheryl Acetate. May Contain: Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891), Iron Oxides (CI 77491, CI 77492, CI 77499), Red 7 Lake (CI 15850).

reviews.headline: Fabulous contour pen
reviews.comments: This is a fantastic and affordable contour. I have used it both on the nose and the rest of the face and it glides on like butter. Blends easily and looks great. I highly recommend.

reviews.headline: Beautiful shades, great multi use product
reviews.comments: I have been looking for a project like this that worked for me, forever. I've been loving this contour stick in tapered. I have trouble with everything looking too orange on my skin tone. This cooler rosey tone is perfect. It's multi purpose as a crease shadow. Its my perfect shade for lip contour/liner. It goes on creamy, looks natural, blends well and lasts. The price point is great. Please Morphe, continue making this product.

I am really loving this contour stick. Its a nice cool tone, precise, and super blendable. Ive been hsing this to sculpt and the sudden heat creamy bronzer to warm up  my skin and theyre a great duo. I am especially liking this for scultping my jaw line.

reviews.headline: Melanated girls beware: bad shades
reviews.comments: Girls with melanin beware: this stick is lacking in shades! I orginally got the "Sculpted" shade thinking it would work for me as I am often described as "lighskin" by other black people but as soon as I blended it into mh skin it disappearedâ€” and not in a good way! So I went up to the "Sharpened" shade, which is the second darkest shade, and that worked like a charm! While this product was easy to use, creamy, lighweight, and overall amazing for me I know that if I am tbe second darkest ahade, then darker than me skin girls might be completly out of luck because of a lack of shade options. They should create a bigger shade lineup so I can reccomend this product with friends and family. Overall I loved this product for me but I can't reccomend it for many of the people I know because of the shades.

faceoff_positive.comments:
Note: This product was sent to me by BZZAgent/Morphe in exchange for my honest review. All opinions and experiences stated are my own.

I am generally a really big fan of cream contour, so I was incredibly excited to try this out.  I don't have a lot of experience with Morphe's face products, and I was overally quite pleasantly surprised by the quality and shade of this contour stick. The shade that I received is a cool-toned brown that works well on my skin tone. I am quite pale, so sometimes contour products pull a bit orange on me, but this particular shade ends up looking quite natural once it's blended out. I would describe the finish of this product as natural, it's not fully matte but it doesn't have any shimmer or sparkle in it that would cause it to be a shiny finish. I have dry skin, so I prefer products with this kind of finish. Overly matte products have a tendency to highlight the drier areas of my face, and this contour stick's finish really helps smooth out any minor dry patches that might be peeking through. I also liked that it didn't cling to any dry patches or hair on my face, which I feel contributed to the overall finish being very flattering.

This contour stick is quite slim, which I am a huge fan of. It was incredibly easy to use this to contour in my nose and brow area, but it is also large enough that it is easy to apply as a cheek or jaw contour as well. Some other contour sticks are quite thick, or deposit too much product in small areas like the nose and brow bone, but Morphe has created a stick that is a perfect size for precise application. 

The formula is creamy and blends out quite easily; I tried using both a brush and a makeup sponge and I found that either works quite well with this particular formula of contour. I personally prefer to use the brush, as I feel that the makeup sponge sheered out the contour a little bit more than I would prefer but I think for a more natural look a blending sponge would be best way to apply this. I was recently traveling and forgot my brushes, and I can confirm that this even blends in quite easily with your fingers in a pinch. I found that this contour lasts pretty well throughout the day, even in hot weather I didn't notice it moving around or fading on my face. I do set my face with both a setting powder and a setting spray, so I can't speak to how well this would last if you don't set your face with some sort of translucent powder after application. 

Overall, I am really enjoying using this contour stick and I can definitely see myself repurchasing this when I run out. I think it is an easy to use product that is quite intuitive and has a solid formula that will work for a lot of skin types. I appreciate that the shade range on this seems to be quite wide, but I do think that adding a few more shades on either end is always appreciated.
faceoff_positive.headline: This might be my new holy grail contour!

faceoff_negative.comments: I really wanted to love this product because the color was perfect - I have pale skin, more neutral, not quite warm or cool. The contour color was a nice ashy taupe, not too brown or muddy. Application was smooth and it didn't appear to displace my foundation, but the list of pros unfortunately ended here. Even after vigorous blending, as I do with any cheek or face product, I was unable to diffuse the product enough for it to be wearable. In some lighting, you could still very clearly see the pattern by which I applied the product along my jaw line. I have sensitive skin, so while the product itself didn't trigger a breakout or anything like that, I can't recommend or use this because it requires too much force to blend.
faceoff_negative.headline: Good color, but formula not great for my skin
